  "prompt": "What are some good websites that will help me for final year project?",
  "response": "There are numerous websites that provide resources and guidance for final year projects across various fields. Here are some highly recommended ones:\n\n1. **GitHub:** Great for finding code repositories and collaboration with other developers. You can also share your project and get feedback from the community.\n\n2. **Stack Overflow:** A huge community of programmers where you can ask questions and find answers related to your project.\n\n3. **IEEE Xplore:** Excellent resource for accessing research papers and articles. It\u2019s particularly useful if your project involves advanced technical concepts or cutting-edge technology.\n\n4. **Coursera and edX:** Offer online courses and specializations from top universities which can provide you with the skills needed to complete your project.\n\n5. **Khan Academy and Codecademy:** Great for learning various programming languages and techniques that might be necessary for your project.\n\n6. **ResearchGate:** Useful for networking with researchers and finding academic papers.\n\n7. **Instructables:** A place to explore tutorials and projects, especially if your project has a DIY aspect.\n\n8. **Google Scholar:** A great tool for finding scholarly articles, theses, books, abstracts, and court opinions.\n\n9. **Project Gutenberg:** Good source for accessing free eBooks related to various subjects which might be useful for background research.\n\n10. **Hackaday:** Offers inspiration and documentation for engineering projects, particularly hardware projects.\n\nRemember to also check out your university's library and online databases\u2014they might have subscriptions to journals and resources that could be invaluable for your project.",
